-ai-conference-dominated-by-openai-and-deepmind/articleshow/130853557.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-kunvar-thaman-solo-indian-researcher-whose-paper-was-accepted-at-an-elite-ai-conference-dominated-by-openai-and-deepmind/articleshow/130853557.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T16:46:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130853715,imgsize-711826.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why do rockets curve after launch instead of going straight? The reason is surprising]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130847237.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/why-do-rockets-curve-after-launch-instead-of-going-straight-the-reason-is-surprising/articleshow/130847237.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/why-do-rockets-curve-after-launch-instead-of-going-straight-the-reason-is-surprising/articleshow/130847237.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T16:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130847201,imgsize-23458.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[1.6 million-year-old bones reveal how the first humans really got their meat]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130849404.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Ancient Kenyan fossils reveal early humans employed a dynamic strategy for meat acquisition, blending hunting with opportunistic scavenging. Evidence of tool marks on bones, alongside predator tooth marks, suggests a sophisticated approach to accessing carcasses. This adaptable foraging, including marrow extraction and meat transport, was crucial for survival and brain development, moving beyond the simple hunter-scavenger debate.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/1-6-million-year-old-bones-reveal-how-the-first-humans-really-got-their-meat/articleshow/130849404.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/1-6-million-year-old-bones-reveal-how-the-first-humans-really-got-their-meat/articleshow/130849404.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T14:32:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130849485,imgsize-1790578.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Need to put British people first’: Row erupts as Shabana Mahmood wants more refugees to come to UK legally]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130854792.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/need-to-put-british-people-first-row-erupts-as-shabana-mahmood-backs-more-legal-refugee-routes-to-uk/articleshow/130854792.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/need-to-put-british-people-first-row-erupts-as-shabana-mahmood-backs-more-legal-refugee-routes-to-uk/articleshow/130854792.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T17:14:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130854914,imgsize-60322.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[London police form 100 officers unit to protect Jewish community amid rise in antisemitic attacks]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/13085184