 reflected on his family’s sacrifices and his early struggles in Sheffield, where he moved at 16. He now plans to invest his prize money in property in Sheffield rather than luxury spending, marking a grounded start to his reign.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/22-year-old-new-snooker-world-champion-reveals-plans-for-major-purchase-worth-half-his-earnings-after-crucible-win/articleshow/130851055.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/22-year-old-new-snooker-world-champion-reveals-plans-for-major-purchase-worth-half-his-earnings-after-crucible-win/articleshow/130851055.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T15:42:02+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Sports Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130851494,imgsize-171692.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Brampton high school team with several Indian-origin teens beats 23,000 students worldwide to win prestigious space contest]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130851362.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Brampton's Central Peel Secondary School students, many of Indian origin, clinched the top prize in the 2026 Gerard K. O’Neill Space Settlement Contest. Their innovative 'Saoirse' project proposed a self-sustaining settlement for 10,000 residents at the Mars-Sun L2 Lagrange point. This marks a historic first for a Canadian team in this prestigious global aerospace competition.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/brampton-high-school-team-with-several-indian-origin-teens-beats-23000-students-worldwide-to-win-prestigious-space-contest/articleshow/130851362.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/brampton-high-school-team-with-several-indian-origin-teens-beats-23000-students-worldwide-to-win-prestigious-space-contest/articleshow/130851362.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T15:38:22+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130851435,imgsize-1149910.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[McGregor vs Holloway UFC 329 comeback fight confirmed? EA Sports teases stunning UFC 6 trailer matchup]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130848525.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Speculation over a Conor McGregor vs Max Holloway rematch for UFC 329 intensified after EA Sports released the UFC 6 trailer featuring a simulated version of their bout, showing Holloway finishing McGregor. The footage, released ahead of International Fight Week, has fuelled talk around McGregor’s potential return after a long injury absence, with Holloway also acknowledging interest in the matchup.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/mcgregor-vs-holloway-ufc-329-comeback-fight-confirmed-ea-sports-teases-stunning-ufc-6-trailer-matchup/articleshow/130848525.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/mcgregor-vs-holloway-ufc-329-comeback-fight-confirmed-ea-sports-teases-stunning-ufc-6-trailer-matchup/articleshow/130848525.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T14:55:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Sports Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130850253,imgsize-697395.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Top 20 tennis stars including Djokovic and Sabalenka protest French Open prize money as boycott talk grows]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130847067.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Tensions between top tennis players and the Grand Slams are escalating ahead of the 2026 French Open, with Aryna Sabalenka warning of a potential boycott over prize money and player welfare. Despite a 9.5% increase at Roland Garros, players argue their revenue share continues to decline, citing inadequate consultation, insufficient welfare provisions, and a growing disconnect between tournament earnings and competitor compensation.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/top-20-tennis-stars-including-djokovic-and-sabalenka-protest-french-open-prize-money-as-boycott-talk-grows/articleshow/130847067.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/top-20-tennis-stars-including-djokovic-and-sabalenka-protest-french-open-prize-money-as-boycott-talk-grows/articleshow/130847067.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T13:34:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Sports Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130848298,imgsize-651299.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[North Korea revises constitution, drops references to reunification with South Korea]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130848052.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/north-korea-revises-constitution-drops-references-to-reunification-with-south-korea/articleshow/130848052.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/north-korea-revises-constitution-drops-references-to-reunification-with-south-korea/articleshow/130848052.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T13:31:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130848281,imgsize-69536.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hantavirus outbreak: Spain allows virus-hit cruise ship to sail to Canary Islands]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130848815.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/hantavirus-hit-cruise-ship-to-sail-to-canary-islands-passengers-to-undergo-medical-screening/articleshow/130848815.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/hantavirus-hit-cruise-ship-to-sail-to-canary-islands-passengers-to-undergo-medical-screening/articleshow/130848815.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T14:14:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130849086,imgsize-217600.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘I prefer hiring Indians’: Dubai-based Emaar founder Mohamed Alabbar praises work ethic and discipline]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130847952.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/i-prefer-hiring-indians-dubai-based-emaar-founder-mohamed-alabbar-praises-work-ethic-and-discipline/articleshow/130847952.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/i-prefer-hiring-indians-dubai-based-emaar-founder-mohamed-alabbar-praises-work-ethic-and-discipline/articleshow/130847952.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T13:18:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130848047,imgsize-617440.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Safety concerns': US to shut Peshawar consulate in Pakistan, to shift operations to Islamabad]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130846710.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The United States is closing its consulate general in Peshawar due to safety concerns for diplomatic staff and resource allocation. While the physical presence is reduced, the US will maintain engagement with Khyber Pakhtunkhwa through its embassy in Islamabad. This decision follows a wave of unrest in Pakistan.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/safety-concerns-us-to-shut-peshawar-consulate-in-pakistan-to-shift-operations-to-islamabad/articleshow/130846710.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/safety-concerns-us-to-shut-peshawar-consulate-in-pakistan-to-shift-operations-to-islamabad/articleshow/130846710.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-06T12:19:54+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130846806,imgsize-860315.cms"/></item></channel></rss>